    "intro": "Interpretation asks what the text means — moving from observation (what does it say?) to the author's intent in his original context and the canonical trajectory it establishes. Hosea 3 is five verses, but they carry four distinct interpretive movements: the divine command and its ground, the redemption price and its theology, the period of restrained discipline, and the eschatological resolution. Where the Hebrew illuminates an English ambiguity, a Greek note is appended as a supplement.",
